body:
Fixes #4373

~I also removed a bit of unused capsule-related implementation~

comment_data.body: It turned out that by making it possible to lookup the class correctly, I inadvertently made it possible to pickle the class (which is correct, although likely to fail on unpickling since `_cython_VERSION_NUMBER` isn't a real module...), which inadvertently made it possible to pickle the instance (which is definitely incorrect). These were only impossible to pickle by luck before
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -1501,13 +1501,29 @@ static PyObject *__Pyx_CoroutineAwait_no_new(PyTypeObject *type, PyObject *args,
 }
 #endif
 
+#if PY_VERSION_HEX < 0x03060000
+// In earlier versions of Python an object with no __dict__ and not __slots__ is assumed
+// to be pickleable by default. Coroutine-wrappers have significant state so shouldn't be.
+// Therefore provide a default implementation
+static PyObject *__Pyx_CoroutineAwait_reduce_ex(__pyx_CoroutineAwaitObject *self, PyObject *arg) {

comment_data.body: I think removing this calls for a separate PR. (Specifically, reverting this PR for whatever potential future reason should not reinstate this code.)
This seems a separate PR as well. I understand that the name change unearthed this issue, but they are not actually otherwise related.

comment_data.body: Note that there might be more than one such module, e.g. when `numpy.random` is imported.

comment_data.body:
True - however, this is run in a srctree test that starts a separate process and imports almost nothing so I think it's safe. I've added an assert to confirm that.

I did try looking up `type(func).__module__` but that fails with type-specs because `__module__` is an accessor rather than a string. So I've reverted to a assuming there will only be one `_cython_` module.

 assert b.funcB.func_globals is b.__dict__
+
+# Test that it's possible to look up the name of the class
+from sys import modules
+for n, mod in modules.items():
+    if n.startswith("_cython_"):  # the internal module..

Fix the name of attributes in the common module

This helps with pickling I hope
Made coroutine wrapper objects explicitly non-pickleable
Also provide a dummy __reduce__ for typespecs

milestone.description:
Goals:
– New version scheme: 3.x instead of 0.x.
– Change default `language_level` from `2` to `3`.
– Change default for `binding` directive from `False` to `True`.
– Fix some Python compatibility issues (if possible, allowing for breaking changes).
